title: Fixed the issue when resuming after mem clean.
message:
Fixed the issue when resuming after mem clean.

root cause:
The method that actually asked the adapter to add new items
added them to the top but the list was sorted.
This caused a reverse order.
Changed the addition to appending and thus the sort ordered was kept.

title: Fixed on resume bug:
message:
Fixed on resume bug:

When memory is cleared (like with 360 security).
The transaction handler is empty, i added a flag
so that i know it hasn't called the featch yet.
Now in the main activity's onCreate i check it
and if it's true i call featch there.
